<HEADLINE>
FT  24 SEP 93 / Commodities and Agriculture: OPEC ministers to meet in
Geneva
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID LASCELLES, Resources Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Oil ministers of the Organisation of Petroleum Exporting Countries gather in
Geneva tomorrow with the oil price languishing just above Dollars 16 a
barrel despite this week's upheavals in Russia, writes David Lascelles,
Resources Editor.
Analysts say that the ministers will have to hammer out an agreement to hold
production at around 24.5m barrels of oil a day - slightly less than the
third quarter peak but 920,000 barrels above the official ceiling - if they
are to provide the market with a firm underpinning.
However, this meeting has been preceded by less kite-flying than usual, and
analysts say the outcome is hard to call. Although the final quarter always
produces a rise in demand, with the onset of winter in the northern
hemisphere, there has been little indication that Opec is getting to grips
with its over-production problems.
The meeting will also have to address the question of how to re-integrate
Kuwaiti output into the production ceiling, and consider the return of Iraq
to the Opec fold.
</TEXT>
