<TEXT>
CEDEL, the Luxembourg-based securities clearing house, is to launch a
service which will allow customers to use US Treasuries as collateral for
its financing facilities and for international settlement.
This is the first time Treasuries will be used as collateral outside the US,
said Mr Michel Vermaerke, a senior manager at Cedel. The service will be
launched on November 3.
