<HEADLINE>
FT  24 SEP 93 / Labour's 'entire credibility' is at stake
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID OWEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
LABOUR'S 'entire credibility' over education is at stake following its
last-gasp decision to delay publication of a discussion document which was
already in the hands of university vice-chancellors, Mr John Patten,
education secretary, said yesterday, David Owen writes.
Mr Patten, who distributed the higher education paper to journalists, said
Labour was in 'chaos' over education and urged Mrs Ann Taylor, shadow
education secretary, to resign.
