<HEADLINE>
FT  23 SEP 93 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Demand for wool is still holding up very well at auctions in Australia and
New Zealand. Clearances are good, with as much as 97% of the offering at
Sydney sold yesterday, though 90% is more typical. Prices are firm and
occasionally a little dearer, with the AWC market indicator up another 2
cents to 433 cents a kg. on September 22, compared with 428 a week before.
Postponement rather than removal of the Garnaut stockpile disposal threat is
seen as a factor helping to bring about a more active market spell, but
longer term anxieties persist
</TEXT>
