FT  23 SEP 93 / International Company News: Lyonnaise des Eaux Dumez halves
net
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN RIDDING
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
LYONNAISE des Eaux Dumez, the French industrial and utility group, yesterday
announced a halving of net profits in the first six months of the year from
FFr711m to FFr342m (Dollars 60m).
The company said the downturn reflected the weakness of the European
construction and property sectors but forecast that full-year net profits
would be higher than the FFr379m. achieved in 1992.
The first-half result was achieved on sales of FFr45.1bn, about the same
level as in the corresponding period last year. Exceptional gains fell from
FFr629m to FFr300m between the two periods.
The group's property division continued to suffer in the adverse economic
climate, reporting a net loss of FFr330m compared with a loss of FFr273m in
the first half of 1992.
Construction losses increased more sharply, rising from FFr4m in the first
six months of last year to FFr139m this year.
The holding and services division, however, raised net profits from FFr566m
to FFr768m.
