CDollars 500m.
Co-Steel, of Toronto, has operated a mini-mill in the US for more than 20
years and has teamed-up with Dofasco, Canada's biggest integrated
steelmaker, in a new mini-mill now being built in Kentucky. Ipsco has yet to
finalise a location for its mill but it may choose Kentucky.
