<TEXT>
BANCA NAZIONALE del Lavoro, the Italian treasury-owned bank, reported parent
company pre-tax profits of L152bn (Dollars 96.9m) for the first six months
of this year, up 111 per cent on the L72bn made in the same period last
year, writes Haig Simonian in Milan.
