<HEADLINE>
FT  23 SEP 93 / UK Company News: River &amp; Mercantile American assets up
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
River &amp; Mercantile American Capital and Income Trust reported a net asset
value of 49.54p per capital share as at August 31.
The figure was marginally ahead of the 49.34p of end-February and
represented an advance of 62 per cent on the August 1992 value of 30.6p.
Attributable revenue for the six months to end-August edged ahead to Pounds
265,000 (Pounds 250,000), equivalent to earnings of 3.53p (3.33p) per income
share.
The second interim dividend is maintained at 1.8p, making 3.6p to date.
